block content
	section#thanks
		.page-header
			h1 Thank you
		p.lead Thank you for purchasing. If you have any questions that are beyond the scope of this documentation, please feel free to contact me.
		p.lead By the way, if you like the plugin, please star it ★★★★★, Thank you so much! :)
		

	section#intro
		.page-header
			h1 Introduction
		p.lead "Flexnav" is a fully responsive jQuery menu/navigation plugin. It was built with Less CSS which makes it easy to modify.

	section#file-structure
		.page-header
			h1 File Structure
		p.lead Within the download you'll find the following file structure and contents
		p Once downloaded, unzip the compressed folder  and you'll see something like this:

		pre.prettyprint
			| flexnav/
			| ├── Docs/
			| ├── Example - Basic/
			| ├── Example - Advanced/
			| └── flexnav/
		ul
			li
				strong "Docs"
				|  folder is where the help documentation is.
			li
				strong "Example - Baic"
				|  contains a simple example.
			li
				strong "Example - Advanced"
				|  contains a much complex example, which also includes Less CSS and CoffeeScript files.
			li
				strong "flexnav"
				|  contains the minified version of flexnav plugin.


	section#quick
		.page-header
			h1 Basic Usage
		p.lead You can refer to 
			strong Example - Basic
			|  folder for code example. All you need to do is write some HTML, and one line jQuery code.
		p.lead Include the CSS and JS file
		p You need jQuery, since it's build on jQuery.
		pre.prettyprint.linenums
			| &lt;!-- include the CSS and JS files --&gt;
			| &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="css/jquery.flexnav.css"&gt;
			| &lt;script src="js/vendor/jquery-1.10.2.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
			| &lt;script src="js/jquery.flexnav.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

		P.lead The Menu:
		pre.prettyprint.linenums
			| &lt;!-- Menu container --&gt;
			| &lt;div class="fn-container fn-dark"&gt;

			| 	&lt;!-- Mobile menu name --&gt;
			| 	&lt;div class="fn-name"&gt;
			| 		&lt;span&gt;Menu&lt;/span&gt;
			| 	&lt;/div&gt;
			| 	&lt;!-- end Mobile menu name --&gt;

			| 	&lt;!-- Button --&gt;
			| 	&lt;div class="fn-button"&gt;
			| 		&lt;span class="fn-bar"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
			| 		&lt;span class="fn-bar"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
			| 		&lt;span class="fn-bar"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
			| 	&lt;/div&gt;
			| 	&lt;!-- end button --&gt;

			| 	&lt;!-- Menu --&gt;
			| 	&lt;div class="flexnav"&gt;
			| 		&lt;ul&gt;
			| 			&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Item 1&lt;/a&gt;
			| 				&lt;ul&gt;
			| 					&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Sub Item 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			| 					&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Sub Item 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			| 				&lt;/ul&gt;
			| 			&lt;/li&gt;
			| 			&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Item 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			| 			&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Item 3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			| 			&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Item 4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			| 			&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Item 5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			| 		&lt;/ul&gt;		
			| 	&lt;/div&gt;
			| 	&lt;!-- end Menu --&gt;

			| &lt;/div&gt;
			| &lt;!-- end Menu container --&gt;


		P.lead Init, with one line jQuery code:
		pre.prettyprint.linenums
			| &lt;!-- init plugin --&gt;
			| &lt;script&gt;
			| $('.flexnav').flexnav();
			| &lt;/script&gt;

		p.lead Again. You can refer to 
			strong Example - Basic
			|  folder for code example. 

	section#usage
		.page-header
			h1 More options Usage
		p.lead There are some options avaiable:
		dt breakpoint: 767
		dd  # Integer: The responsive breakpoint (px) of flexnav
		dt animationSpeed: 250
		dd  #Integer: The speed of slide animation, in milliseconds.
		dt backLabel: 'Back' 
		dd  # String: The text of go back item
		dt useActiveItemAsBackLabel: true
		dd  # Boolean: true or false. If true, the 'Back' text will be replaced with active item name.
		br
		p So you can write you code this way:
		pre.prettyprint.linenums
			&lt;script&gt;
			| $('.flexnav').flexnav({
			| 	breakpoint: 767,
			|	animationSpeed: 250,
			|	backLabel: 'Back',
			| 	useActiveItemAsBackLabel: true
			| });
			&lt;/script&gt;		
		p.lead Examples
		p You can also refer to the Examples - Advanced to see how things work.

	section#features 
		.page-header
			h1 Features
		p.lead How to change the theme scheme?
		p The default is dark theme.
		p To use the ligth theme, you need to do two things:
		li 
			strong Change the CSS.
			|  Use the light theme CSS.
		li
			strong Change the theme scheme class of menu container. 
			|  Use 
			strong fn-light
			|  instead of fn-dark, like: 
		br
		pre.prettyprint.linenums
			| &lt;!-- Menu container --&gt;
			| &lt;div class="fn-container fn-light"&gt;

		p.lead If you want more color schemes you can modify the Less file to build your own. And there is 
			strong 9 preset color schemes.



